{
  "text": "where the coefficient \u03ba is precisely the coefficient of the gravitational Chern-Simons term defined in (4). [CITATION_1] However, recall that in the presence of a domain wall at x = 0, \u03ba is not a constant but a function \u03ba(x) which jumps across the domain wall, i.e., \u03ba(x >> 2 ) = \u03ba + and \u03ba(x << \u2212 2 ) = \u03ba \u2212 (where is the thickness of the domain wall). The diffeomorphism invariance of the full theory (bulk plus domain wall) imposes the constraint [CITATION_2] . Taking this into [CITATION_3] There is also a term lower order in derivatives of the form [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] ",
